水冷得刺骨  但当地女人很热情
The water is cold as hell, but... the women are very warm.

169
00:08:43,210 --> 00:08:45,460
克莱尔怕是不会乐意
Oh, I'm not sure what Claire would think about that.

170
00:08:45,460 --> 00:08:47,540
带她一起
Well, bring her along.

171
00:08:48,520 --> 00:08:50,170
那里有很多艺术家
It's crawling with artists out there.

172
00:08:50,180 --> 00:08:52,000
说不定她能找到喜欢的
She might find something she likes.

173
00:08:55,280 --> 00:08:56,900
总统先生  我很好奇
Mr. President, I'm intrigued.

174
00:08:56,900 --> 00:08:59,890
你一到美国对我说的第一个字就是"不"
The first thing you say to me is "No" the second you arrive,

175
00:08:59,890 --> 00:09:02,130
紧接着又邀请我去你的乡间别墅
and the next moment you're inviting me to your dacha.

176
00:09:02,920 --> 00:09:04,110
你到底是个什么样的人
Who am I dealing with?

177
00:09:04,290 --> 00:09:07,640
我刚来就说清楚了  你有什么疑惑
I believe I was clear when we first met. What confuses you?

178
00:09:07,640 --> 00:09:10,160
我们的代表团谈这些事谈了好几个月
Our delegations have been discussing these issues for months.

179
00:09:10,160 --> 00:09:12,670
没错  但谈不代表达成一致
Yes, but discussions are not the same as commitment.

180
00:09:13,350 --> 00:09:14,980
我现在告诉你
And, uh, I'm telling you now.

181
00:09:16,100 --> 00:09:17,410
我们不会达成一致
There will be no commitment.

182
00:09:18,100 --> 00:09:19,940
这你打电话就能告诉我了
You could've told me that on the phone.

183
00:09:22,860 --> 00:09:26,130
我以为你邀我来是想弥补对我的侮辱
I assumed you were undoing an insult by having me here.

184
00:09:26,400 --> 00:09:27,840
什么侮辱
What insult is that?

185
00:09:28,130 --> 00:09:30,790
你的前两任都没邀请我来过华盛顿
Two of your predecessors never invited me to Washington.

186
00:09:30,980 --> 00:09:33,030
这次峰会不是走过场
This summit is not just for show.

187
00:09:33,120 --> 00:09:35,480
我希望能朝着和平的目标迈出一大步
I want to make meaningful strides toward peace.

188
00:09:35,490 --> 00:09:38,460
历史告诉我们  中东地区是没救了
The Middle East is hopeless. History tells us that.

189
00:09:38,650 --> 00:09:41,040
我是在给你创造历史的机会
I'm offering you the chance to make history.

190
00:09:41,040 --> 00:09:42,170
我就跟你说实话了
I'll be honest with you,

191
00:09:42,170 --> 00:09:44,590
毕竟你好心好意请我来
because you've been kind enough to invite me to your country.

192
00:09:46,570 --> 00:09:49,930
中东和平  对俄罗斯毫无利益可言
Russia has nothing to gain from peace in the Middle East.

193
00:09:50,080 --> 00:09:54,300
更重要的是  和美国合作也毫无利益
And more importantly, nothing to gain from working with America.

194
00:09:55,630 --> 00:09:58,030
以色列一向不信任我们
Israel has always distrusted us.

195
00:09:58,440 --> 00:09:59,490
你指望这有所改变吗
You expect that to change?

196
00:09:59,490 --> 00:10:01,780
我们希望能慢慢建立信任
We expect to build trust over time.

197
00:10:04,190 --> 00:10:06,840
你们今早和大使们的会面怎么样
How was your meeting with the ambassadors this morning?

198
00:10:08,030 --> 00:10:09,900
阿鲁里大使给我打电话了
Ambassador Aruri called me.

199
00:10:10,900 --> 00:10:11,920
他们有疑虑
They have their doubts,

200
00:10:11,920 --> 00:10:14,190
但我们希望他们能愿意考虑
but we encouraged them to keep an open mind.

201
00:10:14,190 --> 00:10:15,760
他说他十分担忧
He described it as grave concerns.

202
00:10:15,760 --> 00:10:17,580
等我们确定了他们自然会适应...
They will acclimate as soon as we establish--

203
00:10:17,580 --> 00:10:21,210
你丈夫直接向以色列和巴勒斯坦提议了吗
Has your husband made direct overtures to Israel and Palestine?

204
00:10:21,510 --> 00:10:23,060
所有正式通讯
All formal communication

205
00:10:23,070 --> 00:10:25,070
都经由国务院处理
has been handled through the State Department.

206
00:10:25,070 --> 00:10:27,360
但你丈夫不可能认为他们会顺从吧
But your husband can't possibly believe they'll comply.

207
00:10:27,360 --> 00:10:29,090
先生们  为了让谈话进行下去
Gentlemen, for the purposes of these talks,

208
00:10:29,090 --> 00:10:31,260
请你们叫他总统
I'd appreciate it if you refer to him as the president,

209
00:10:31,260 --> 00:10:32,670
而不是"我丈夫"
not as my husband.

210
00:10:32,980 --> 00:10:34,390
当然  大使女士
Of course, Madam Ambassador.

211
00:10:34,390 --> 00:10:36,510
而且你该向杜兰特国务卿发问
And you really should be addressing Secretary Durant.

212
00:10:36,510 --> 00:10:39,280
她比我更能代表总统的意见
She speaks on his behalf more than I do.

213
00:10:40,340 --> 00:10:43,820
抱歉  国务卿女士  请继续吧
Our apologies, Madam Secretary. Please, continue.

214
00:10:44,210 --> 00:10:49,260
我们想把细节梳理完  请翻到12页
We'd like to finish reviewing the specifics, so page 12, please.

215
00:10:49,570 --> 00:10:52,690
总统先生  我们已经在多个方面展开了合作
Mr. President, we're already working together on several fronts:

216
00:10:52,840 --> 00:10:55,780
防核扩散协议  打击恐怖主义  朝鲜
nonproliferation, the War on Terror, North Korea.

217
00:10:55,780 --> 00:10:58,360
为什么中东就偏偏不行呢
I don't see any reason that the Middle East should be any different.

218
00:10:58,360 --> 00:11:00,760
-因为这是美国的计划  -不是那样
- Because it's an American plan. - It's not an American plan.

219
00:11:00,760 --> 00:11:03,290
-我保证条件平等  -保证
- I'm promising equal terms. - Oh, promises.

220
00:11:03,290 --> 00:11:06,010
{\pos(382,284)}{\an3}1978年在戴维营军事基地
卡特总统促成埃及与以色列之间
签署了《戴维营协议》

221
00:11:03,290 --> 00:11:04,740
卡特总统保证双方平等参与
Carter promised equal involvement,

222
00:11:04,750 --> 00:11:06,010
最后签协议的时候却没叫我们
then shut us out of Camp David.

223
00:11:06,260 --> 00:11:07,600
波斯尼亚战争  克林顿也是如此
Clinton did the same with Bosnia.

224
00:11:07,600 --> 00:11:08,710
现在我是总统
I'm the president now.

225
00:11:08,720 --> 00:11:10,140
这次不会那样了
That won't happen this time.

226
00:11:10,140 --> 00:11:12,820
直到18个月之后  你下台
Until 18 months from now, when you are replaced.

227
00:11:16,330 --> 00:11:17,730
我很嫉妒  维克多
I'm jealous, Viktor.

228
00:11:19,560 --> 00:11:22,910
你不用向任何人汇报  没有任何对手
You don't answer to anyone. You have no real opposition.

229
00:11:22,910 --> 00:11:25,970
你也知道大选结果会怎么样
You know exactly how every election is gonna turn out.

230
00:11:25,980 --> 00:11:28,780
美国可不是这样
Well, it's not like that in the United States.

231
00:11:29,280 --> 00:11:31,540
我不竞选  是因为我
I'm not running because I can

232
00:11:31,540 --> 00:11:34,990
能做到总统候选人做不到的事  比如这份提议
do things a candidate can't do, like this proposal.

233
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:37,560
得了吧  总统先生  你我都知道你会参选的
Please, Mr. President, we both know you'll run.

234
00:11:38,890 --> 00:11:42,450
不过能不能赢  谁知道呢
Now, whether you win... Who knows?

235
00:11:42,760 --> 00:11:45,440
直说吧  你究竟想要什么
Brass tacks. If you could have anything, what would it be?

236
00:11:48,110 --> 00:11:50,020
我没什么想要的
I came with nothing to ask.

237
00:11:51,450 --> 00:11:54,620
你这种人如果没有胃口  是不会赴宴的
Men like you don't show up for dinner without an appetite.

238
00:11:59,680 --> 00:12:02,100
我旅途劳顿  总统先生
It was a long flight, Mr. President.

239
00:12:03,470 --> 00:12:04,740
先谈到这儿吧
How about we stop here for now.

240
00:12:04,740 --> 00:12:05,910
我休息休息眼睛
I rest my eyes a bit and

241
00:12:05,910 --> 00:12:08,080
等精神好点再想想这个提案
put some thought into this with a fresh mind.

242
00:12:09,390 --> 00:12:12,930
没准能想出我要什么
Maybe I'll... think of something I want.

243
00:12:13,980 --> 00:12:15,460
等晚宴的时候再谈
We'll talk more later, at dinner.

244
00:12:15,460 --> 00:12:17,260
可以啊  如果你想这样
Of course, if that's what you prefer.

245
00:12:20,350 --> 00:12:23,050
他知道自己要什么  就是要别人求他
He knows exactly what he wants, but he needs to be wooed.

246
00:12:23,050 --> 00:12:24,580
不过也算有进展
Progress, nonetheless.

247
00:12:24,880 --> 00:12:27,850
不经过"也许"  是没法把"不"变成"好"的
You can't turn a "No" to a "Yes" without a "maybe" in between.

248
00:12:37,910 --> 00:12:38,730
先生们
Gentlemen...

249
00:12:39,600 --> 00:12:41,260
副局长来了
Deputy Director coming through.

250
00:13:18,330 --> 00:13:20,880
奥尔西  跟我来
Orsay? Come with me, please.

251
00:13:21,940 --> 00:13:22,950
我们抓到亚设了
We got Asher.

252
00:13:23,640 --> 00:13:25,770
凌晨两点半  他要吓死了
Two-thirty this morning. He was scared to death.

253
00:13:26,330 --> 00:13:29,400
15分钟之后  他给了我们6TB的压缩文件
By 2:45, he gave us six terabytes of compressed files.

254
00:13:29,400 --> 00:13:31,690
两千五百万美国电话电报公司用户的信息
All 25 million AT&T users.

255
00:13:32,010 --> 00:13:33,610
你的货存错地方了
You hid your goodies with the wrong person.

256
00:13:33,610 --> 00:13:35,840
-不止他一个  -我觉得就他一个
- He wasn't the only one. - I think he was.

257
00:13:36,870 --> 00:13:39,460
我的指控已经撤销了  你没法逮捕我
You can't arrest me for charges that have already been dropped.

258
00:13:39,460 --> 00:13:41,410
放松  没人要逮捕你
Relax. No one's arresting you.

259
00:13:42,780 --> 00:13:43,910
从我手上的报告看
From the reports I've been getting,

260
00:13:43,910 --> 00:13:45,860
你工作一直很出色
you've been doing an excellent job for us.

261
00:13:47,440 --> 00:13:49,260
好好继续干下去  前途无量
If you stay straight, sky's the limit.

262
00:13:50,130 --> 00:13:51,400
接大任务  领导自己的团队
Bigger assignments. Manage your own team.

263
00:13:51,400 --> 00:13:52,850
你知道我也是走投无路才来的
You know I wouldn't be here if I had a choice.

264
00:13:52,860 --> 00:13:54,390
但你现在有选择了
But you do have a choice.

265
00:13:55,820 --> 00:13:58,550
你可以充分利用这第二次机会
You can make the most of this second chance if you want to,

266
00:13:58,550 --> 00:14:02,380
但你得证明你想要这机会
but... you have to prove you want it.

267
00:14:04,170 --> 00:14:06,630
-名字  -我不求别的
- Names. - That's all I've ever wanted.

268
00:14:08,100 --> 00:14:08,880
不行
No.

269
00:14:13,040 --> 00:14:14,870
亚设会供出名字的
Asher's going to give up names.

270
00:14:16,380 --> 00:14:18,080
-他不会那么做的  -或许会
- He wouldn't do that. - He might.

271
00:14:18,790 --> 00:14:19,730
但愿他们不会抖出些
Let's hope none of them tell us

272
00:14:19,730 --> 00:14:21,910
我们还不知道的你的罪行
about anything we didn't charge you for.

273
00:14:24,440 --> 00:14:27,750
你在这里可以有大好未来  嘉文
You have a future here, Gavin.

274
00:14:30,740 --> 00:14:32,860
好了  回去吧
All right. Back to it.

275
00:14:36,100 --> 00:14:37,440
好好工作
Keep up the good work.

276
00:14:39,130 --> 00:14:40,940
我们得去晚宴了
We have to wine and dine.

277
00:14:41,250 --> 00:14:43,970
-要迷倒他们  -他们  还有谁
- Charm them senseless. - Them? Who's the other?

278
00:14:43,970 --> 00:14:47,410
博奇  他压着《美就法》不肯动弹
Birch. He's sitting on AmWorks like his ass is afraid of the sun.

279
00:14:47,410 --> 00:14:49,320
别逼我跟鲍勃聊天
Please don't make me talk to Bob.

280
00:14:49,320 --> 00:14:51,930
你只用负责佩特罗夫  我来对付鲍勃
You just focus on Petrov. I'll deal with Bob.

281
00:14:52,380 --> 00:14:54,430
打扰一下  先生  我们准备好了
Excuse me, sir. We're all set.

282
00:14:54,430 --> 00:14:56,170
佩特罗夫总统在黄色椭圆厅了
President Petrov is in the Yellow Oval.

283
00:14:56,170 --> 00:14:57,430
谢谢  卡莉斯塔
Thank you, Calista.

284
00:15:01,150 --> 00:15:03,740
我可能需要弥补一下凯茜
I think I may need to do some damage control with Cathy.

285
00:15:03,740 --> 00:15:06,090
-为什么  -我一直努力对她恭敬
- Why? - I've been trying to be deferential,

286
00:15:06,090 --> 00:15:08,890
但她可能觉得我是自视高她一等
but I think it's coming off as patronizing.

287
00:15:09,350 --> 00:15:12,040
-本就有这风险  -我知道
- Well, that was the risk. - I know.

288
00:15:12,260 --> 00:15:13,620
她觉得受威胁了吗
Is she feeling threatened?

289
00:15:13,940 --> 00:15:16,620
威胁  不会  可能有点被抢了风头
Threatened, no. Possibly overshadowed.

290
00:15:17,200 --> 00:15:18,490
我的关注度太高
I think I'm getting too much attention

291
00:15:18,490 --> 00:15:20,750
凯茜不跟我一队
and it's tough to be effective

292
00:15:20,750 --> 00:15:22,020
我会举步维艰
when I don't have Cathy on my team,

293
00:15:22,020 --> 00:15:23,800
我可能得讨她欢心
so I may need to win her over.

294
00:15:24,070 --> 00:15:26,390
别忘了今晚的主角应该是谁
Well, let's not forget where the focus is tonight.

295
00:15:26,890 --> 00:15:29,150
我什么时候不能一心二用了
Since when can't I do two things at once?

296
00:15:29,860 --> 00:15:31,670
-你歪了  -什么
- You're crooked. - What?

297
00:15:34,630 --> 00:15:37,410
-准备好去战斗了吗  -是的
- Ready for battle. - Yes.

298
00:16:15,590 --> 00:16:17,500
美利坚合众国副总统  唐纳德·布莱斯
The Vice President of the United States, Donald Blythe.

299
00:16:17,500 --> 00:16:19,470
-总统先生  欢迎  -副总统先生
- Mr. President. Welcome. - Mr. Vice President.

300
00:16:19,470 --> 00:16:20,330
谢谢
Thank you.

301
00:16:22,240 --> 00:16:23,860
佩特罗夫总统  欢迎
President Petrov, welcome.

302
00:16:23,860 --> 00:16:24,780
倍感荣幸
It's a pleasure.

303
00:16:27,760 --> 00:16:28,560
你美极了
You look beautiful.

304
00:16:28,560 --> 00:16:30,180
马马虎虎吧
Oh, it's serviceable.

305
00:16:30,470 --> 00:16:32,860
-你也和往常一样明艳动人  -谢谢
- You look fantastic, as always. - Thank you.

306
00:16:32,860 --> 00:16:36,490
大家的注意力都会在你身上  不是他们
All eyes at the table will be on you, not them.

307
00:16:38,120 --> 00:16:41,170
门多萨参议员  不久就是总统候选人了
Senator Mendoza. Soon to be candidate Mendoza.

308
00:16:41,170 --> 00:16:42,440
这就谣言四起了
The rumor mill begins.

309
00:16:42,440 --> 00:16:44,680
你最开始是跟着里根  对吗
You started with Reagan, no?

310
00:16:44,690 --> 00:16:46,240
他84年竞选团队的一员
Staffed on his '84 campaign.

311
00:16:46,240 --> 00:16:49,510
他办公室里有张里根总统戴牛仔帽的照片
He has a portrait of the Gipper in his office wearing a cowboy hat.

312
00:16:50,400 --> 00:16:51,600
那时男人还有男子气概
When men were men.

313
00:16:57,110 --> 00:16:58,140
鲍勃  我有个想法
Bob, I had a thought.

314
00:16:58,140 --> 00:16:59,980
大卫·布兰切特在军事委员会
Dave Blanchek is on Armed Services and--

315
00:16:59,980 --> 00:17:01,600
我不想让后面的人久等
I don't want to hold up the line.

316
00:17:03,290 --> 00:17:05,750
-总统先生  很荣幸  -移下博奇的位置
- Mr. President, a pleasure. - I want to move Birch.

317
00:17:05,750 --> 00:17:07,580
门多萨换到我边上来
Put Mendoza next to me instead.

318
00:17:07,580 --> 00:17:10,320
艾伦  收拾得挺利索
Alan. You clean up well.

319
00:17:10,580 --> 00:17:11,970
场合需要
Class by association.

320
00:17:12,020 --> 00:17:14,120
-你的女伴呢  -我一个人来的
- Where's your date? - I don't have one.

321
00:17:14,120 --> 00:17:15,810
你想得话  我可以陪你走进去
I can walk you in too, if you'd like.

322
00:17:15,810 --> 00:17:17,690
不了  那不是要毁了你的照片
No. Wouldn't want to ruin the picture.

323
00:17:20,110 --> 00:17:21,470
我们的特殊客人
Ah, our special guests.

324
00:17:21,470 --> 00:17:23,130
很高兴你们能参加晚宴
I'm so delighted you could be with us.

325
00:17:23,130 --> 00:17:25,260
感谢你们能来  总统先生
Thank you so much for coming. Mr. President.

326
00:17:25,320 --> 00:17:28,110
过了这么久才有机会在同一张桌子上坐下
It's taken us too long to sit at the same table.

327
00:17:28,190 --> 00:17:32,440
你们在闭门会议时讨论了我们的问题吗
Did you discuss our issues in the closed talks?

328
00:17:32,530 --> 00:17:34,130
我们讨论了很多事
We discussed many things.

329
00:17:34,130 --> 00:17:36,990
但我们的担忧呢
But specifically our concerns?

330
00:17:37,010 --> 00:17:39,160
我们列出的问题你们谈过了吗
Was anything on our list discussed?

331
00:17:39,160 --> 00:17:41,440
-先照相吧  -好主意
- Why don't we take a photo first? - Good idea. Hm?

332
00:18:02,450 --> 00:18:05,000
维克多  告诉我  你在恋爱吗
Viktor, tell me. Are you in love?

333
00:18:05,490 --> 00:18:08,510
爱什么的我不知道
I don't know about... love, but...

334
00:18:10,770 --> 00:18:12,980
但我在学习享受离婚的乐趣
I'm learning to enjoy being divorced.

335
