00:38:28,100 --> 00:38:30,430
他亲你  有点过分了
That kiss was... too much.

683
00:38:30,430 --> 00:38:32,310
不  他那是非常过分
No, that's just pushing buttons.

684
00:38:33,030 --> 00:38:35,420
俄国人就喜欢这么惹别人
The Russians love to do that.

685
00:38:36,460 --> 00:38:37,310
晚安
Good night.

686
00:38:39,100 --> 00:38:41,270
我觉得不能相信他  凯茜
I don't think he's to be trusted, Cathy.

687
00:38:41,850 --> 00:38:44,940
尤其是今晚之后  让我不禁思考
Especially after tonight. And it made me think...

688
00:38:47,550 --> 00:38:48,420
继续说
Go on.

689
00:38:49,930 --> 00:38:52,770
这让我重新考虑了弗兰西斯的计划
It made me wonder about Francis' plan.

690
00:38:52,770 --> 00:38:57,380
我认为与佩特罗夫合作未必是好主意
I'm not sure that it's a good idea to be partnered with Petrov.

691
00:38:57,580 --> 00:39:01,060
而且我们还破坏了与以色列和巴勒斯坦的关系
In the meantime, we alienate Israel and Palestine.

692
00:39:03,900 --> 00:39:08,080
私下里告诉你  我也同意
Well... between you and me, I agree.

693
00:39:10,570 --> 00:39:11,590
过来坐
Sit with me.

694
00:39:13,290 --> 00:39:15,230
那你想采取什么不同的办法呢
What would you do differently?

695
00:39:17,700 --> 00:39:18,660
这个
Well...

696
00:39:20,770 --> 00:39:23,810
如果最终目标是向约旦河谷派军的话
If the goal is to get troops into the Jordan Valley,

697
00:39:23,810 --> 00:39:27,520
达到目标的办法可不止一种
well, then there's more than one way to skin that cat.

698
00:39:27,850 --> 00:39:29,540
多国部队吗
A multinational force?

699
00:39:30,140 --> 00:39:31,670
我倾向通过联合国
I would go through the UN.

700
00:39:32,720 --> 00:39:33,770
维和部队吗
Peacekeeping?

701
00:39:34,730 --> 00:39:36,720
但俄罗斯会否决的
You wouldn't get past Russia's veto.

702
00:39:37,400 --> 00:39:40,180
也许有个办法  但是...
There might be a way, but...

703
00:39:41,520 --> 00:39:44,580
那样你就有很重的任务了
you'd have a lot of responsibility on your shoulders.

704
00:39:45,710 --> 00:39:48,410
如果你能指点我  我相信我能处理好
Well, if you can give me guidance, I'm sure I can handle it.

705
00:39:50,710 --> 00:39:55,150
以前有联合维和决议案的先例
There is precedent with the Uniting for Peace Resolution.

706
00:39:55,150 --> 00:39:58,290
我们就是借这个  绕过苏俄发动了朝鲜战争
We used it to get around the Russians for the Korean War.

707
00:40:03,770 --> 00:40:06,530
-全部吗  -从波兰到英国
- The whole thing? - From Poland to the UK.

708
00:40:06,540 --> 00:40:08,810
我希望整个导弹防御系统都拆除
I want the entire missile defense system gone.

709
00:40:08,810 --> 00:40:11,700
你知道那是为了防御朝鲜和伊朗
You know that's there to defend against North Korea, against Iran.

710
00:40:11,700 --> 00:40:13,830
但比起朝鲜伊朗  却离我国更近
And far closer to my borders than theirs.

711
00:40:13,830 --> 00:40:16,560
我只是希望你派几千部队进入约旦河谷
I'm asking for a few thousand troops in the Jordan Valley.

712
00:40:16,560 --> 00:40:19,030
你却要求我废除欧洲的防御系统
You're asking me to dismantle Europe's defense system.

713
00:40:19,030 --> 00:40:21,190
你真正的要求是让美国部队
What you're really asking for is American forces

714
00:40:21,190 --> 00:40:22,730
进入高加索南部
just south of the Caucasus.

715
00:40:23,080 --> 00:40:25,500
你肯定已经想好了战略规划
You must have a strategic play in mind.

716
00:40:25,510 --> 00:40:27,560
这是为了地区稳定
This is about stability in the region.

717
00:40:27,560 --> 00:40:30,550
你是想巩固在这个地区的地位吧
You're trying to consolidate your foothold in the region.

718
00:40:31,440 --> 00:40:34,680
黑海  哈萨克斯坦  车臣  克里米亚
The Black Sea, Kazakhstan, Chechnya, Crimea.

719
00:40:35,020 --> 00:40:38,630
拜托  别扯什么和平来侮辱我了
So, please... don't insult me with peace.

720
00:40:41,080 --> 00:40:43,490
无论你的战略目标是什么
Whatever your strategic goals may be,

721
00:40:45,060 --> 00:40:46,730
导弹防御系统是我的
the missile defense system is mine.

722
00:40:48,310 --> 00:40:52,140
维克多  我邀请你来华盛顿的目的很纯粹
Viktor, I invited you to Washington with pure intentions,

723
00:40:52,140 --> 00:40:55,260
就是为了我们能一起进餐  学习信任对方
so that we could break bread and learn to trust one another.

724
00:40:55,260 --> 00:40:58,620
弗兰西斯  一顿美妙的晚餐
Francis, I don't get softened up

725
00:40:58,620 --> 00:41:01,580
和与美丽的女士共舞不会让我心软的
by a nice dinner and dancing with a beautiful woman.

726
00:41:03,230 --> 00:41:04,630
你问我想要什么
You asked me what I want.

727
00:41:05,240 --> 00:41:06,880
我告诉你了
Well... I told you.

728
00:41:10,370 --> 00:41:11,440
这样吧
I'll tell you what.

729
00:41:11,900 --> 00:41:13,500
现在我要去睡会儿了
It's my turn to get some sleep.

730
00:41:13,500 --> 00:41:15,600
等头脑清醒点再处理这些事吧
Let's attack all this with a fresh mind.

731
00:41:15,600 --> 00:41:17,510
我们还没抽完雪茄呢
We've barely smoked our cigars.

732
00:41:19,310 --> 00:41:22,050
我们不是那种无节制的人  对吧
We're not men of excess, though, are we?

733
00:41:23,810 --> 00:41:24,740
不是吗
Aren't we?

734
00:41:29,220 --> 00:41:30,160
不是
No, no.

735
00:41:31,140 --> 00:41:32,230
不  你说得对
No, you're right.

736
00:41:35,170 --> 00:41:37,050
这一晚上抽得够多了
Enough smoke for one evening.

737
00:41:52,210 --> 00:41:53,710
你打算怎么办
What are you going to do?

738
00:41:55,020 --> 00:41:56,070
不知道
I don't know.

739
00:41:57,380 --> 00:41:58,860
想办法与他妥协吧
Try to meet him halfway.

740
00:42:01,920 --> 00:42:03,360
凯茜和我聊了一会儿
Cathy and I were talking.

741
00:42:04,300 --> 00:42:06,770
也许以色列人和巴勒斯坦人是对的
Maybe the Israelis and the Palestinians are right.

742
00:42:06,770 --> 00:42:08,570
我们应该考虑从他们下手
We should consider starting with them.

743
00:42:09,000 --> 00:42:11,690
利用联合国向俄罗斯施压
Use the United Nations to put pressure on Russia.

744
00:42:11,740 --> 00:42:14,680
-怎么施压  -联合维和
- How? - Uniting for Peace.

745
00:42:15,260 --> 00:42:16,420
让联合国大会推翻
General Assembly overrides

746
00:42:16,420 --> 00:42:18,520
俄罗斯在安理会投的否决票
a Russian veto in the Security Council.

747
00:42:19,740 --> 00:42:22,250
即便成功  也只会激怒他们
Well, that'll just antagonize them even if it works.

748
00:42:22,250 --> 00:42:23,110
何况不可能成功
And it won't.

749
00:42:23,120 --> 00:42:25,570
也许呢  凯茜似乎认为会成功
Well, it might work. Cathy seems to think it could.

750
00:42:26,180 --> 00:42:28,000
我以为你对这计划有信心
I thought you believed in this plan.

751
00:42:28,840 --> 00:42:31,850
我们只是在考虑别的选择
We were just... brainstorming alternatives.

752
00:42:32,300 --> 00:42:35,010
我付出了这么多努力  怎么能前功尽弃
Well, I've worked too hard on it just to abandon it.

753
00:42:36,980 --> 00:42:38,400
好吧  你知道怎么最好
Okay, you know best.

754
00:43:01,290 --> 00:43:02,200
你介意吗
Do you mind?

755
00:43:04,550 --> 00:43:05,340
什么
What?

756
00:43:05,830 --> 00:43:06,720
关灯
The light.

757
00:43:19,750 --> 00:43:20,890
弗兰西斯
Francis.

758
00:43:23,250 --> 00:43:24,300
他是个恶棍
He's a thug.

759
00:43:25,030 --> 00:43:26,680
很聪明  但也还是个恶棍
Smart, but he's still a thug.

760
00:43:26,980 --> 00:43:28,390
别向他屈服
Don't cower to him.

761
00:43:38,000 --> 00:43:38,970
在我的家乡
Where I come from,

762
00:43:38,970 --> 00:43:42,470
我们会把生鸡蛋放进番茄汁里  然后喝掉
we drop a raw egg into some tomato juice and drink that.

763
00:43:42,920 --> 00:43:44,590
还好我不来自你的家乡
Luckily, I don't come from there.

764
00:43:46,680 --> 00:43:47,910
那份工作很适合道格
That's a perfect job for Doug.

765
00:43:47,910 --> 00:43:49,750
真不明白他为什么拒绝
I can't imagine why he'd turn it down.

766
00:43:49,960 --> 00:43:51,410
他觉得是我们在背后安排的
He thinks we were behind it.

767
00:43:51,910 --> 00:43:54,040
我告诉他并没有  但恐怕他不相信我
I told him we weren't, but I don't think he believes me.

768
00:43:54,240 --> 00:43:55,910
说他不需要辅助训练
Said he doesn't need training wheels.

769
00:43:56,640 --> 00:43:59,190
我要你继续偶尔去看看他
Well, I want you to still stop in from time to time and see him.

770
00:43:59,200 --> 00:44:00,020
是  先生
Yes, sir.

771
00:44:01,370 --> 00:44:03,860
国防部长来了吗  让他进来
Is the Secretary of Defense here? Send him in.

772
00:44:06,790 --> 00:44:08,660
-总统先生  -我们没多少时间
- Mr. President. - We don't have much time.

773
00:44:08,660 --> 00:44:11,250
佩特罗夫90分钟后到  我们得谈欧洲的情况
Petrov gets here in 90 minutes. We need to talk Europe.

774
00:44:54,140 --> 00:44:56,540
答案是可以
The answer is yes.

775
00:44:56,940 --> 00:44:59,630
可以接受你的部分但并非全部要求
To some, not all, of what you asked.

776
00:45:00,970 --> 00:45:01,550
好吧
I see.

777
00:45:01,550 --> 00:45:04,020
我准备对导弹防御系统进行大规模削减
I'm prepared to scale back significantly.

778
00:45:04,030 --> 00:45:08,700
我得先跟我的团队及我们的北约同盟国商量下
Now, I have to speak to my team first and my allies in NATO,

779
00:45:08,700 --> 00:45:11,260
但我相信我们可以在波兰和捷克共和国
but I'm confident that we can do something meaningful

780
00:45:11,260 --> 00:45:13,320
作出重要调整
in Poland and the Czech Republic.

781
00:45:13,320 --> 00:45:15,820
我们双方可以就细节做进一步协商
Now, our people can work out the specifics.

782
00:45:15,820 --> 00:45:18,930
但无论我们达成怎样的共识
And whatever it is we decide and agree on,

783
00:45:18,930 --> 00:45:21,020
都不能让公众知晓
the public cannot know.

784
00:45:25,680 --> 00:45:29,210
我醒来时满嘴都是昨晚抽过的雪茄味
I woke up with the taste of those cigars in my mouth.

785
00:45:29,860 --> 00:45:32,200
让我想到了古巴导弹危机和肯尼迪
Thinking of Cuba and Kennedy.

786
00:45:32,860 --> 00:45:34,440
我可不会像赫鲁晓夫
I won't be humiliated the way

787
00:45:34,440 --> 00:45:36,380
在土耳其导弹问题上那样被羞辱
Khrushchev was with Turkey.

788
00:45:32,850 --> 00:45:36,380
{\pos(382,286)}{\an3}古巴导弹危机时
美国最终从土耳其撤军
比苏联晚一些  而且是秘密撤军
表面上来看是这场危机的胜利者

789
00:45:37,180 --> 00:45:38,550
你不能将我的提议
Well, you can't possibly compare

790
00:45:38,550 --> 00:45:40,590
与当时的事件相提并论
what I'm proposing to what happened then.

791
00:45:40,590 --> 00:45:42,600
只有你同意对外宣布
I can only consider a partial scale-back

792
00:45:42,600 --> 00:45:43,970
我才会接受部分削减
if you announce it.

793
00:45:46,570 --> 00:45:48,780
这场新闻发布会是关于约旦河谷问题
This press conference is about the Jordan Valley.

794
00:45:48,780 --> 00:45:50,840
调整导弹防御系统的重点是削减
The most important thing about the missiles is the scale-back,

795
00:45:50,840 --> 00:45:51,620
不是公关
not the PR.

796
00:45:51,620 --> 00:45:54,410
我的人民需要知道我不是空手而归
My people would know I walked away with something.

797
00:45:54,410 --> 00:45:58,570
而且对外宣布后  我就能逼你信守诺言
And, by announcing it, I can keep you to your word.

798
00:45:58,580 --> 00:46:01,820
我可是做出了相当大的让步  维克多
I am more than meeting you halfway, Viktor.

799
00:46:08,150 --> 00:46:11,600
你知道苏联解体最大快人心之处是什么吗
You know what the best part of the Fall of the Soviet Union was?

800
00:46:12,890 --> 00:46:13,940
是汽车
The cars.

801
00:46:15,400 --> 00:46:17,650
你坐过拉达牌汽车吗
Have you ever been in, um... a Lada?

802
00:46:18,350 --> 00:46:19,710
拉达  没有
Lada? No, I haven't.

803
00:46:19,710 --> 00:46:22,300
没有吗  那是世上最烂的车
No? Oh. It's the worst car ever built.

804
00:46:22,560 --> 00:46:24,180
很小  很袖珍的一辆车
Tiny, little thing, you know.

805
00:46:24,180 --> 00:46:27,970
车开过坑颠一下  你的头就会撞到车顶
Your head would hit the ceiling when you hit a pothole.

806
00:46:28,220 --> 00:46:30,380
暖气永远不制热
And the heat never worked.

807
00:46:31,060 --> 00:46:32,340
还没有空调
And no air conditioning.

808
00:46:32,340 --> 00:46:35,360
大夏天皮肤都要粘到座位上
You know, your skin would stick to the seats in the summer.

809
00:46:35,360 --> 00:46:37,350
简直是可移动的棺材
It was a coffin on wheels.

810
00:46:37,420 --> 00:46:42,290
但苏联解体后  就能买到雷克萨斯
But then, after the Fall, we got the Lexus.

811
00:46:43,490 --> 00:46:46,470
有空调  自动车窗
Temperature control. Automatic windows.

812
00:46:46,760 --> 00:46:48,570
而且空间很大
And so much room.

813
00:46:48,570 --> 00:46:52,150
我第一次上我前妻  就是在一辆雷克萨斯里
First time I fucked my ex-wife, in a Lexus.

814
00:46:52,330 --> 00:46:53,890
在拉达里你想都不要想
You could never do that in a Lada.

815
00:46:53,890 --> 00:46:54,720
空间根本不够
No space.

816
00:46:56,280 --> 00:46:57,780
现在情况是这样  总统先生
You see, Mr. President.

817
00:46:59,210 --> 00:47:00,700
我想要雷克萨斯
I want the Lexus.

818
00:47:02,270 --> 00:47:04,420
你却向我推销拉达
And you're trying to sell me a Lada.

819
00:47:31,010 --> 00:47:33,130
我去让你的车队来接你
I'll have them bring your motorcade around.

820
00:47:36,620 --> 00:47:38,560
但还有新闻发布会
But the... press conference.

821
00:47:41,130 --> 00:47:42,050
对啊
Right!

822
00:47:43,420 --> 00:47:45,070
我忘得一干二净
I'd completely forgotten.

823
00:47:46,390 --> 00:47:49,030
不过今天不做新闻发布会也不要紧
But I think we're gonna be okay without one today.

824
00:47:50,970 --> 00:47:53,090
回程一路顺风  总统先生
Have a safe journey home, Mr. President.

825
00:48:02,620 --> 00:48:05,490
多谢你的款待  总统先生
Thank you for your hospitality, Mr. President.

826
00:48:15,750 --> 00:48:17,350
给我接国务卿
Give me the Secretary of State.

827
00:48:31,770 --> 00:48:33,550
总统将单独发表讲话
The President will be speaking alone.

828
00:48:33,550 --> 00:48:35,190
不举行联合新闻发布会
No joint conference.

829
00:48:37,330 --> 00:48:39,460
总统很快就来
The President will be out shortly.

830
00:48:45,610 --> 00:48:48,270
昨晚  我有幸在白宫招待了
Last night, I had the pleasure of hosting

831
00:48:48,280 --> 00:48:50,900
几位非常尊贵的宾客
some very special guests here at the White House.

832
00:48:51,450 --> 00:48:53,250
几位真正的俄罗斯爱国者
True Russian patriots

833
00:48:53,250 --> 00:48:56,280
他们展现了他们国家最优良的美德
who exhibit the very best that their country has to offer.

834
00:48:56,950 --> 00:48:59,560
他们的名字是  娜迪亚·托伦科尼卡瓦
Their names: Nadya Tolokonnikova,

835
00:48:59,700 --> 00:49:03,190
玛莎·艾柳金纳和彼得·韦奇洛夫
Masha Alyokhina and Pyotr Verzilov.

836
00:49:03,440 --> 00:49:04,960
你们应该已经知道
As you're all aware,

837
00:49:05,040 --> 00:49:07,070
他们敢于挑战佩特罗夫总统
they stood up to President Petrov,

838
00:49:07,200 --> 00:49:10,970
并强迫他倾听他不愿听到的真相
and forced him to listen to the truths that he didn't want to hear.

839
00:49:12,660 --> 00:49:16,040
这令我深受震撼
And, well, that had a profound effect on me.

840
00:49:16,510 --> 00:49:17,840
因为这让我意识到
Because it made me realize

841
00:49:17,840 --> 00:49:19,560
我也要勇于与他抗衡
that I need to stand up to him as well.

842
00:49:19,560 --> 00:49:21,340
我们的国家也一样
As does our country.

843
00:49:21,790 --> 00:49:23,290
我邀请总统来访
When I invited the President here,

844
00:49:23,290 --> 00:49:26,090
是旨在结交盟友
I set out hoping to find a partner.

845
00:49:26,390 --> 00:49:30,320
但佩特罗夫总统的要求让我明白
But the demands that President Petrov made proves to me

846
00:49:30,650 --> 00:49:33,470
和平并非他的第一诉求
that peace is not a priority for him.

847
00:49:33,890 --> 00:49:37,130
和平不该通过买卖取得
Peace should not have to be bought.

848
00:49:37,370 --> 00:49:40,070
和平本就该足矣
Peace should be its own reward,

849
00:49:40,220 --> 00:49:41,840
不论他是否是我们的盟友
and we will achieve it,

850
00:49:41,990 --> 00:49:44,010
我们终会迎来和平
with or without him.

851
00:49:44,050 --> 00:49:45,360
非常感谢
Thank you very much.

852
